lse, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-18T16:44:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/08/ss_cad1ccc375ff5f280af980321ee5454b586bfd7a.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The SteamWorld series is one of my favorites in gaming today, a loosely connected collection of titles that each take a popular genre and add their own spin on it. Thunderful is having a <a href=\"https://www.gog.com/en/promo/20240917_thunderful_publisher_sale\">publishing sale at GOG</a>, and the headline deal here is <em>SteamWorld Heist 2</em>, which debuted last month and is <a href=\"https://www.gog.com/en/game/steamworld_heist_ii\">on sale at GOG for $20.99</a> (was $29.99). </p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em>SteamWorld Heist 2</em> is an excellent 2D turn-based tactics game that takes heavy inspiration from <em>XCOM</em> \u2014&nbsp;i", "id": 1168786, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/good-deals/452837/steamworld-heist-2-sale-build-quest-dig", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The entire SteamWorld library, including SteamWorld Heist 2, is on sale at GOG", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-18T16:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"Orcs, shown here in the Player\u2019s Handbook (2024), are now part of the core rules for player characters. | Image: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.mikepape.com/&quot;&gt;Mike Pape&lt;/a&gt;/Wizards of the Coast\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.mikepape.com/&quot;&gt;Mike Pape&lt;/a&gt;/Wizards of the Coast\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/05-027.orc_Mike_Pape-copy.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption>Orcs, shown here in the Player\u2019s Handbook (2024), are now part of the core rules for player characters. | Image: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.mikepape.com/&quot;&gt;Mike Pape&lt;/a&gt;/Wizards of the Coast</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\">The concept of race has been removed from <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/dnd-dungeons-dragons\">Dungeons &amp; Dragons</a>\u2019 new <a href=\"http", "id": 1168787, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/dnd-dungeons-dragons/452438/new-players-handbook-uses-species-not-race", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Race becomes species in D&#038;D, but that\u2019s not the only change in the new Player\u2019s Handbook", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-18T15:56:31+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24898296/Sequence_03.00_57_44_18.Still001RC.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Production for <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23851279/one-piece-live-action-season-2-netflix-release-cast-news\">season 2 of Netflix\u2019s live-action <em>One Piece</em></a> is well underway, but probably still quite a ways off. Despite that fact, the streaming service did have a few details to share about the new season during its Geeked Week presentation, including a behind-the-scenes teaser that it released on Wednesday. </p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The teaser is hosted by Jeff Ward, who plays the <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23859960/one-piece-live-action-cast-buggy-clown-jeff-ward\">fan favorite vill", "id": 1168788, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/entertainment/452889/one-piece-season-2-netflix-live-action-trailer-teaser-bts", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "One Piece season 2\u2019s behind the scenes trailer is mysterious but still looks great", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-18T14:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/NUP_203843_00050.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\">During the last few years, space epics have ruled streaming and the small screen. Shows like <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/reviews/23815585/telltale-the-expanse-game-review-episodes\">The Expanse</a></em>, <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23294222/for-all-mankind-season-3-review-episodes-finale\">For All Mankind</a></em>, and <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23873497/foundation-season-2-finale-ending-apple-tv-plus-interview\">Foundation</a></em> have won awards, provoked profound conversations, and made sci-fi fans out of skeptics. Building on the legacies of earlier series like the <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23991388/battlestar-galac", "id": 1168139, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/tv/452455/the-ark-sci-fi-tv-show-review-watch", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Ark is a perfect throwback to an age when sci-fi didn&#8217;t have to be so serious", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-18T13:42:03+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/horizon_zero_dawn.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Sony Interactive Entertainment will release <em>Horizon Zero Dawn Remastered</em> for PlayStation 5 and Windows PC, according to <a href=\"https://www.esrb.org/ratings/40023/horizon-zero-dawn-remastered/\">a new rating from the Entertainment Software Ratings Board</a>, which detailed the unannounced game. The ESRB description of <em>Horizon Zero Dawn Remastered</em> is <a href=\"https://www.esrb.org/ratings/34770/horizon-zero-dawn/\">identical to the original</a> <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/2017/2/20/14576092/horizon-zero-dawn-review-ps4-playstation-4-sony-guerrilla-games\">Horizon Zero Dawn</a></em> that first launched on PlayStation 4 in 2017.</p>\n\n<p class=", "id": 1167663, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/playstation/452732/horizon-zero-dawn-remaster-ps5-pc", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Horizon Zero Dawn remaster coming to PS5, PC", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-18T13:08:14+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Photo: Nintendo\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/22701350/switch_oled_model.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>Nintendo, notoriously secretive, has so far said almost nothing on the record about its next game console. As the Nintendo Switch celebrated its seventh birthday in March 2024, questions about how much longer it will last are natural: Seven years is a typical lifespan for a console generation, Switch sales are <a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2023/05/09/nintendo-full-year-earnings-2023-switch-sales-plunge-22percent.html\">falling fast</a>, and the technology powering the console is showing its age.</p>\n\n<p>Behind the scenes, however, <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23633001/nintendo-switch-2-release-date-2024-backward-compatibility\">Nintendo is g", "id": 1167664, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/nintendo/23899504/nintendo-switch-2-release-date-power-name-games", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Everything we know about \u2018Switch 2,\u2019 Nintendo\u2019s next-gen console", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-18T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/ufo50_ss04.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\">The issue I had reviewing <em>UFO 50</em> is not the issue you will have playing it.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Presenting itself as an anthology of all 50 games developed by UFO Soft, a fictional game studio active from 1982-89, <em>UFO 50</em> is all about breadth and variety. The player is presented with the entire catalog of games from the outset, and they can choose to play them in any order, and for any length of time. These are not WarioWare-style microgames, mind you. They are fully-fledged titles of varying length, ranging from arcade-style side-scrollers to fully developed dungeon crawlers, all presented in the 8-bit style of the imagined ", "id": 1167665, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/review/452079/ufo-50-review-pc", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "UFO 50 was terrible to review but incredible to play", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-18T11:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/ss_23a0adb29ad9ee7c0029d8b599521dd8629775f5.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em>Wild Indigo Ranch</em> is built out of two great concepts: a chill, <em>Stardew Valley</em>-esque ranch simulator, and the core gameplay loop of survival sandbox games. The player arrives on the Western frontier to collect their inheritance from a mysteriously deceased uncle. Turns out that inheritance is Wild Indigo Ranch, a run-down shack on a patch of dirt surrounded by bandits, coyotes, and the nefarious Grit Corp.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">This game has co-op for up to four players, and while I played it solo, I can see myself returning with my husband or a good friend in tow. This town, luckily, is big enough for the b", "id": 1166565, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/review/452385/wild-indigo-ranch-pc-review", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Wild Indigo Ranch balances cozy ranching with cowboy action", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-18T04:01:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/jlee_240904_1001_pogo_shiny_wobbuffet.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><strong>Wobbuffet</strong>, the patient Pok\u00e9mon from Johto, can be found in the wild in <em